RACE.FOOTNOTES: VLADISLAV settled up close in the three path, bid between foes under a ride early around the far turn, took the lead while in the three path into the stretch, bumped with an outer challenger nearing the eighth pole, but stayed on and held off another late closing foe in the closing stages. EXECUTIVE SEARCH set the pace in the two path, but lost the lead midway around the far turn, and yielded into the stretch. AN OBJECTION LODGED BY THE RIDER OF JOURNEYMAN AGAINST THE RIDER OF VLADISLAV FOR INTERFERENCE DOWN THE BACKSTRETCH WAS DISALLOWED.
